				\begin{document}$${{{{{\rm{RBF}}}}}}=\,\frac{\sum {{{{{{\rm{AUC}}}}}}}_{{{{{{\rm{Cortex}}}}}}}}{\Delta t\cdot \sum {{{{{\rm{AIF}}}}}}}$$\end{document}RBF=∑AUCCortexΔt⋅∑AIFWith AUCCortex being the summed signal of the renal cortex ROI, AIF being the signal time curve of the central blood vessel and Δt the delay between two image frames. Total renal blood flow (tRBF) was then obtained from the sum of both RBFs for the left and the right kidney. For calculation of glomerular filtration rates based on slice spectroscopy data, pH-shifted peaks were assigned to the anatomical regions of the kidneys, signal time curves for cortex and pelvis extracted and used for calculation of tGFR-values.
